The paper discusses a theoretical framework for mutation-based testing methods, which are commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the formalization of behavioral differences of programs, which relates to systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of mutation-based testing methods to fault localization and program repair, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
